Imo State immediate-past Commissioner for Foreign Affairs, Fabian Ihekweme, on Wednesday, dumped the All Progressives Congress for the Peoples Democratic Party. The defection took place at the Kanu Nwankwo stadium in Owerri at a reception organised by the PDP to welcome home the National Secretary of the party, Samdaddy Anyanwu, alongside the national leadership led by Iyorchia Ayu. Also received officially to the PDP, was another top stakeholder, and a former Chairman of the PDP, in the state, Charles Ezekwem, who abandoned the APC, and returned to the PDP with his supporters.